\sum_{k+j=n,0\le k,j\le n}\binom{2k}{k}\binom{2j}{j}=4^n
\sum_{k=0}^\infty\binom{2k}{k}x^k=\frac1{\sqrt{1-4x}},
x^n
\begin{align}\sum_{a_1+a_2+\cdots+a_k=n,0\le a_1,a_2,\cdots,a_k\le n}\binom{2a_1}{a_1}\binom{2a_2}{a_2}\cdots\binom{2a_k}{a_k}\qquad(\star)\end{align}
\left(\frac1{\sqrt{1-4x}}\right)^k=(1-4x)^{-\frac 12 k}.
(1-4x)^{-\frac 12 k}=\sum_{n=0}^\infty\binom{-\frac 12k}{n}(-4x)^{n},
(\star)=\binom{-\frac 12 k}{n}(-4)^n=\frac{\left(-\frac 12 k\right)\left(-\frac 12 k-1\right)\left(-\frac 12 k-n+1\right)}{n!}\cdot (-4)^n=\frac{\left(\frac 12 k\right)\left(\frac 12 k+1\right)\left(\frac 12 k+n-1\right)}{n!}\cdot 4^n.
m\in\mathbb N
k=2m.
(\star)=\binom{m+n-1}{n}\cdot 4^n
k=2m-1.
(\star)=\frac{\binom{2n}{n}\cdot\binom{2m+2n-2}{2n}}{\binom{m+n-1}{n}}
k=2
